The SWM Board faithfully performs its duties and responsibilities on the IEC campaign, specifically the following:

13. Prepare IEC campaign materials for distribution which should be crafted in accord to the level of understanding of the stakeholders in order to saturate the target stakeholders in its entirety;


14. Develop training modules which should be patterned after those already developed by the Solid Waste Association of the Philippines (SWAPP);


15. Collaborate IEC campaigns with the Barangay officials to achieve proper coordination and synchronization.  Establish focal persons for each barangays who shall be responsible in the arrangements and schedules of IEC campaigns; and


16. Follow-up on IECs be conducted regularly in the whole municipality to ensure that the information and education drive is applied consistently and continuously.

20. Instruct the BAC to strictly comply with the mandatory posting of the updated APP, NOA and other relevant information in the GPPB online portal to promote accountability and transparency in the conduct of Emergency Procurement under the Bayanihan Act; 

21. Warranty provision should be included in the contract/Purchase Order to guarantee that the contractor shall perform all his responsibilities stipulated therein; and


22. Henceforth, instruct the Municipal Accountant to be more vigilant in the processing of claims on 20% DF by requiring compliance in the submission of complete documentary requirements before effecting payment to establish validity and propriety of the transactions and to avoid suspension/ disallowance in audit.

